/*
This program's purpose is to play music! using either Instrument.BASS or Instrument.PIANO

We can input a string array of notes, each note you want to play is determinable by the format of 
number for octave at beginning, in between the two | is the notes played which are mapped to piano keys of the same letter. - are rests
the | are ignored 
the input array is length specific. it loops in multiples of 26

"5|eeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeefeDe-|"
when multiple keys are needed at once we simply maintain the same string
"5|eeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeefeDe-|"
and add onto that same string
"5|eeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeefeDe-|3|--c---c---c---c---c---c---|"
this will play these notes simultaneously within a single note

we can have as many notes playing simultaneously as we would like (though I imagine its not terribly efficient using code.org cloud computing)

each verse is seperated by array commas (fairly self explanatory) (a limitation of code.org scene class is that pauses can only go as low as 0.1 seconds)

the duration of the song cannot exceed around 120 seconds due to limitations of code.org
if the input string exceeds 46 verses, it will truncate when played 
  */
